        <h2 class="font-montserrat font-bold text-2xl md:text-3xl text-[#1e3a5f] mb-6">How Broker Finance Works</h2>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A finance broker is an independent intermediary who compares loan options from multiple lenders on your behalf. Unlike a dealer, a broker is not tied to a single dealership or a small panel of finance providers. Nik Finance, for example, compares options from over 130 lenders including major banks like NAB, St George, and Macquarie, credit unions, specialist vehicle finance lenders, and non-conforming lenders for borrowers with impaired credit.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">A broker submits a single application and then identifies the most competitive option from their lender panel based on your credit profile, income, loan amount, and vehicle details. The broker earns a commission from the lender on settlement — you pay nothing for the broker's service. The key difference is that the broker's commission is typically a flat rate or a fixed percentage of the loan amount, not a variable margin on top of the rate. This means the broker has no incentive to inflate your rate.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Importantly, a broker consultation happens away from the dealership. There is no salesperson sitting across the desk, no pressure to sign today, and no tying of the finance decision to the vehicle purchase decision. This separation of the buying decision and the finance decision is one of the most valuable aspects of using a broker.</p>
        <p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed mb-4">Nik Finance also provides a pre-approval service. This means you walk into the dealership already knowing your budget, your rate, and your repayments. You can negotiate purely on the vehicle price without worrying about finance. If the dealer offers to beat your pre-approved rate, great — use their finance. If they cannot, you already have approval ready to go.</p>
        </section>
