        <details class="group border border-gray-200 rounded-xl overflow-hidden mt-3"><summary class="flex items-center justify-between cursor-pointer p-6 bg-white hover:bg-gray-50 transition-colors"><h3 class="font-montserrat font-semibold text-[#1e3a5f] pr-8 text-left">What about novated leases through dealers?</h3><svg class="w-5 h-5 text-[#10b981] flex-shrink-0 group-open:rotate-180 transition-transform" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" viewBox="0 0 24 24"><path stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" stroke-width="2" d="M19 9l-7 7-7-7"/></svg></summary><div class="p-6 pt-0 border-t border-gray-100"><p class="text-gray-700 font-lato font-light leading-relaxed">Dealers do not typically arrange novated leases. A novated lease requires your employer's involvement and is usually arranged through a salary packaging provider or a finance broker. If a dealer offers a novated lease, it is likely through a third-party provider and may carry higher costs.</p></div></details>
